r5u870 (0.11.0+dfsg-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Hijack and improve package for possible inclusion in Debian/sidux.
  * Remove debian/postinst.modules.in and debian/preinst.modules.in, these
    maintainer scripts are far better of being generated by dh_installmodules.
  * Build-depend on debhelper (>= 6), drop cdbs.
  * Improve descriptions in debian/control*.
  * Add debian/rules.modules to take care of module source build.
  * Bump debian/compat to 6.
  * Add debian/watch file.
  * Add debian/r5u870-source.links to establish default module-assistant
    settings.
  * Rewrite debian/rules using debhelper centric style. Add a get-orig-source
    target to reproduce creation of the dfsg free orig tarball.
  * Remove debian/r5u870-source.install, it is no longer needed.
  * Add patches to fix various build issues (see patch header for specific
    details):
    - sanitize_makefile.patch
    - dont_redefine_V4L2_CID_LASTP1.patch
    - fix_build_for_2.6.26.patch

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sun, 30 Mar 2008 23:53:01 +1000

